gomodel:SYNGO_5476  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1b: Hippocampal slices cotransfected with HA-ASIC2a showed localization to dendritic shafts and spines.\n\nFigure 1d: ASIC2 identified in synaptosomes prepared from Myc-ASIC2a transgenic mice.\n\nFigure 2: ASIC2a associates with PSD-95 through its PDZ-binding domain.\n\nFigure 3: PSD-95 increases ASIC2a in spines.\n\nFigure 5: Endogenous ASIC2 enriches in synaptosomes and coimmunoprecipitates with ASIC1.\n\nFigure 8: Eliminating ASIC2 decreases the density of dendritic spines.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: \"Representative Western blots of total lysate (L) and synaptosomal fraction (S) of whole brain from wild-type and Myc-ASIC2a transgenic mice.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5476" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

